		<h3 class="groff">
			groff (GNU troff)
		</h3>
		<p>
			The <a class="term" href="glossary.xhtml#gnu">GNU</a> project wrote the <span class="cmd">groff</span> utility as a
			reimplementation of <span class="cmd">ditroff</span>, which encompassed the functionality of the historical <a
				class="term cmd" href="glossary.xhtml#nroff">nroff</a> and <a class="term cmd" href="glossary.xhtml">troff</a>
			utilities.  Its first version was released in 1990, and it is still actively maintained.
		</p>
		<p>
			<span class="cmd">groff</span> is significant in that it is the predominant implementation of <a class="term cmd"
				href="glossary.xhtml#nroff">nroff</a> and <a class="term cmd" href="glossary.xhtml">troff</a> on contemporary
			UNIX operating systems.  It significantly shepherded the development and evolution of <span class="lang">mdoc</span>.
		</p>
